SECTION 3: ENFORCEMENT & VIOLATIONS

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.1 WHAT CONSTITUTES VIOLATION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Commercial use WITHOUT a valid Commercial License:
  ❌ Using for revenue-generating purposes
  ❌ Deployed by registered business entity
  ❌ Accepting payment from customers/clients
  ❌ Any monetization whatsoever

Breach of Attribution:
  ❌ Removing copyright headers from source files
  ❌ Hiding footer attribution in deployed app
  ❌ Removing README attribution
  ❌ Obscuring the original author's work

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.2 ENFORCEMENT PROCESS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 1: DETECTION
The Licensor may discover violations through:
  • Scanning public GitHub repositories
  • Crawling deployed instances
  • Community reports
  • Direct audits

STEP 2: FORMAL NOTICE
Violator receives email notice within 48 hours of detection:
  • Specific violation(s) identified
  • Evidence provided
  • Cure period offered (see below)
  • Contact information for resolution

STEP 3: CURE PERIOD
  • First violation: 7 days to cure
  • Second violation: 3 days to cure
  • Third+ violation: 0 days (immediate action)

STEP 4: NON-COMPLIANCE ACTION
If violation is not cured:
  • License automatically TERMINATED
  • Takedown notice issued
  • Deployment/access revoked
  • Legal action initiated

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.3 LEGAL DAMAGES
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Violations constitute willful copyright infringement under the Indian
Copyright Act, 1957. The Licensor reserves the right to pursue:

  💰 FINANCIAL DAMAGES:
     • $500-$2,500 USD per day of continuous violation
     • $10,000 USD per instance of removed copyright header
     • $25,000-$50,000 USD per hidden/obscured attribution block
     • Retroactive royalties for all months of unlicensed commercial use
       (calculated at 15% of gross revenue as penalty rate)

  ⚖️ LEGAL REMEDIES:
     • DMCA takedown notices to hosting providers
     • Injunctive relief to cease operations immediately
     • Seizure of domain or server access
     • Recovery of all legal fees and court costs

  📋 TAX & REGULATORY:
     • Report to tax authorities if GST evasion evident
     • Notification to business registrars/regulators

UNLIMITED LIABILITY: There is no cap on damages claimed. The Licensor will
pursue maximum remedies available under law.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.4 BURDEN OF PROOF
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The implementer (you) bears the burden of proving:
  • Your use qualifies for Free Tier
  • You have valid Commercial License
  • All attribution is properly maintained
  • Revenue reporting is accurate and complete

Simple deployment for a registered business defaults to violation unless
proven otherwise.

